item.dc:creator: @purelion6679 purelion6679
item.description:
@purelion6679 wrote:

hello, im new to java but im not as dumb as some of these other newbs who appear to be nothing but little kids who dont even understand how to open client.java lol…

anyways, i have been working on my project of making a private server but first i want to make it a little more realistic (by realistic i mean the game parameters and rules similar to the real rs) and i decided to use pimpscape source. I found this a great source to play around with while learning java. although the source is full of bugs, i dont think its so bad that i should scrap it and find another.

ook enough of long introductions lol…anyways, my problem is i want to make the combat more realistic-and by realistic i mean, work similar to how the real RS system works…there are three parts that i need to fix:

first bug, to make the player always facing the engaged NPC or other player, and vice-versa, to make NPC’s that aggro to players always facing them…

second bug, to correctly aggro certain NPC’s (obviously monsters such as dragons and giants ect…) when you walk near enough.

third bug for combat, is the ranging and magic…making the using of runes and arrows work correctly.

last bug is to fix the combat animations for range and magic…e.g. the arrow flying through the air, or the spell animation when cast…

This is a huge request i realize, and ive spent hours analyzing the combat system as it is (which in my opinion, appears almost half-assed) nonetheless im sure the creator spent countless hours writing pimpscape. what i would like is maybe a few suggestions on how i can go about changing the code, or a site with free java programming tutorials suitable for such a large scale recoding project thanks a bunch.

Read full topic
